📦 FOLDER STRUCTURE

smart-parking-system/
├── main.py                  # Main script to run the system
├── parking_slot_detector.py # Core logic for detection
├── parking_slot_config.json # Parking spot coordinates
├── samples/                 # Sample video footage (.mp4)
├── masks/                   # Binary mask images for slots
├── static/                  # Output images or generated media
├── README.md                # Project documentation
├── requirements.txt         # Python dependencies
└── venv/                    # Virtual environment (not pushed to GitHub)

---

🚀 GETTING STARTED

Follow the steps below to set up and run the project locally:

---

1️⃣ Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/harishankar/smart-parking-system.git
cd smart-parking-system

---

2️⃣ Create and Activate a Virtual Environment

python -m venv venv

For Windows:
venv\Scripts\activate

For macOS/Linux:
source venv/bin/activate

---

3️⃣ Install Dependencies

pip install -r requirements.txt

---

4️⃣ Add Sample Files

Place your parking lot video (e.g., parking_1920_1080_loop.mp4) in the samples/ folder.

Ensure you also have:

masks/mask_1.png — Binary mask image for slot detection

parking_slot_config.json — Contains parking slot positions

---

5️⃣ Run the System

python main.py
🖥️ The system will process the video and show parking availability in real-time.

---

🛠 FEATURES

✅ Detect available and occupied parking slots
✅ Binary masking and polygonal slot mapping
✅ Real-time video feed analysis
✅ Easily configurable slot layout (JSON)
✅ Supports any custom video feed or camera

